---
description: Core architecture & process rules for Waypoint Writer
alwaysApply: true
---

# Architecture rules

- Layers: Features → Domain / Data interfaces → Persistence. **Domain never imports
  SwiftUI or SwiftData** (SwiftLint enforces the SwiftUI ban).
- Features depend on protocols (`any SubmissionRepository`, `ContentGenerating`),
  never concrete persistence types.
- No business rules in `View.body`. Logic in ViewModel/Domain.

# Process rules

- Spec-first: no user-visible behavior without a spec in `specs/`. Update the spec
  Verification block and `docs/feature-inventory.md` when behavior changes.
- Test-first for domain & ViewModels. `Tests/Unit` before UI polish.
- Project is generated: run `xcodegen generate`; never commit `.xcodeproj`.
- Build/test with scheme `WaypointWriterCI`.

# Layout (phone vs iPad)

- Detect landscape with `verticalSizeClass == .compact`.
- Distinguish phone vs iPad with `UIDevice.current.userInterfaceIdiom`, **not**
  horizontal size class alone (Pro Max landscape ≠ iPad).

# UI test identifiers

- Convention `screen.element`, centralized in `Support/AccessibilityIDs.swift`.

# Accessibility

- Every interactive control: label, optional hint, stable identifier, ≥44pt target.
- Latest manual audit lives in `accessibility/audits/`.
